The paper deals with mechanism design and allocation of goods, which are topics that fall under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The use of polynomial time algorithms and the agent-order matrix suggest a connection to computational complexity and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of duality and optimization, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper mentions the bandwidth allocation setting, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
